==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pontee
<hw>Pon*tee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pontil</ets>, <ets>pontis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Glass Making)</fld>
<def>An iron rod used by glass makers for manipulating the hot glass; --
called also, <altname>puntil</altname>, <altname>puntel</altname>,
<altname>punty</altname>, and <altname>ponty</altname>. See
<er>Fascet</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pontic</ent>⟦br⟧
